items.summary: Chelsea's winless run extended to four games after a 2-1 defeat to Atalanta in the Champions League, with manager Enzo Maresca admitting his side have to do better after collecting just two points from their last four matches.

source.title: Maresca: Chelsea 'have to do better' as winless streak stretches on with Atalanta loss

items.summary: Liam Delap suffered a shoulder injury against Bournemouth but scans revealed no fracture, while Cole Palmer is being carefully managed and was rested for the Atalanta trip as part of his gradual return to full fitness.

source.title: Enzo Maresca Reveals Latest Liam Delap, Cole Palmer Injury Updates

items.summary: Chelsea have been drawn away to Charlton Athletic in the FA Cup third round, giving them a London derby as they look to bounce back from their recent poor form.

source.title: FA Cup holders Crystal Palace to visit non-league Macclesfield in third round
